# Code ownership for the AI-native SDLC.
#
# Most of the tree can be authored and reviewed by the dev agents. The paths
# below are HUMAN-OWNED guardrails: changes to gates, eval, tests, security
# config, and IaC require the human owner's review even though merge is
# otherwise autonomous on green (docs/AI_NATIVE_SDLC_DESIGN.md §3.1, R2).
#
# Solo start: a single human owner. Add an @agents team here later when the
# dev agents have their own GitHub identity.

# Default owner for everything
*                           @Jarod-Smithy

# Product code (agents will co-own once they have a team identity)
/services/                  @Jarod-Smithy
/frontend/                  @Jarod-Smithy
/sdlc-agents/               @Jarod-Smithy

# ── Human-owned guardrails (prevent agents weakening their own checks) ──
/.github/                   @Jarod-Smithy
/.github/workflows/         @Jarod-Smithy
/.pre-commit-config.yaml    @Jarod-Smithy
/eval/                      @Jarod-Smithy
/tests/                     @Jarod-Smithy
/infra/                     @Jarod-Smithy
/CODEOWNERS                 @Jarod-Smithy
/.github/CODEOWNERS         @Jarod-Smithy
